N:abyssal-game-studio
D:Run an engine-agnostic, evidence-gated game-production harness for a vertical slice, feature, economy change, or release: BMAD-GDS production, survey-grounded research, fair monetization, deterministic systems engineering, adversarial QA, and live-ops readiness. Use for game production spanning research through release gates; not isolated engine bugs, assets, or feedback-only triage.
G:game-production game-studio bmad-gds survey fair-monetization deterministic-systems adversarial-qa live-ops accessibility

U[5]:
  Game vertical slices or release changes requiring research through operations
  Fair monetization and quantitative economy validation without P2W or dark patterns
  Engine-agnostic deterministic replay, performance, memory, input, and pathing contracts
  Twenty-loop adversarial QA spanning seven player archetypes
  Rollback-ready live-service production with non-overridable QA and operations vetoes

S[7]{n,action,details}:
  1,Create the immutable run root,Use <repo-root>/.harness/abyssal-game-studio/<run-id>/ and version corrections instead of editing published artifacts.
  2,Run P0 BMAD-GDS intake,Create production brief task manifest and bounded role inputs one next artifact at a time.
  3,Run P1 evidence and experience,Use survey with six provenance-backed comparables and create world interaction readability accessibility artifacts.
  4,Run P2 policy then systems,Use pm; before purchase require direct price contents functional impact region/tax/refund information and fairness result; reject P2W paid random rewards deceptive direct pricing unclear direct pricing hidden odds/acquisition conditions and loss-targeted/loss-induced offers; `references/role-contracts.json` is the typed source of truth; require deterministic p50/p90 source/sink counterplay simulation evidence.
  5,Run P3 engineering,Require engine-neutral deterministic replay and measured performance memory input and pathing contracts.
  6,Run P4–P5 gates,Execute qa-backed 20-loop A1–A7 adversarial QA then validate telemetry rollback and operations readiness.
  7,Honor vetoes and bounded re-entry,QA FAIL or operations STOP-SHIP cannot be overridden; allow at most two evidence-backed cycles then start a new P0 run.
